{"TopicId":209695,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"How do you fix leaks in space?","CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T18:29:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T18:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPassing through a meteor shower your ship takes several holes in the hull, some too small to see.\u00A0 What is the best way to fix it?\u00A0 Do spray on products like polyurethane, etc work in vacuum?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T19:26:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Meteor shower\u0022 usually means \u00221 grain of sand and two grains of dust in every 100 cubed kilometers of otherwise empty space.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would have to be very unlucky to encounter \u003Cem\u003Eanything\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if you did, there are two most likely outcomes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou spaceship was ripped open like a can of tuna. Everyone die.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a small hole leaking air. Slap a piece of duct tape on it to stop the leak. Then gather supplies for permanent fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T19:27:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCigarettes to find, duct tape to fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T19:59:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173211\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662748179\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPassing through a meteor shower your ship takes several holes in the hull, some too small to see.\u00A0 What is the best way to fix it?\u00A0 Do spray on products like polyurethane, etc work in vacuum?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBig hole? You are F\u0027d.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmall leak? Find the leak via sound or flow vis and slap a patch onto it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T20:03:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any way to paint the outer hull with polymers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T23:04:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPrevention: use mylar/Al foil as a screen.\u00A0 Dust particles hit the screen and explode, hopefully into pieces too small to bother the craft.\u00A0 As far as I know, this is already in use.\u00A0 And I\u0027m not sure any craft has ever needed evasive action while going through the asteroid belt (early ones couldn\u0027t perform any).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need assistance finding the leak (presumably by sound), duct tape will work fine.\u00A0 And you probably have the aero-grade tape on board, which should be even more effective.\u00A0 Air pressure will hold it in place, but I\u0027m sure somebody will want a \u0022permanent fix\u0022.\u00A0 Said fix will likely lose more air (assuming you remove the patch) than the patch would ever leak out.\u00A0 Also removing the patch may be difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is unfortunate that the only steel hulls I\u0027ve heard of in space are all stainless steel.\u00A0 Otherwise I\u0027d recommend using a magnet as a short term patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-09T23:36:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662764666\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I\u0027m not sure any craft has ever needed evasive action while going through the asteroid belt (early ones couldn\u0027t perform any).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022asteroid belt\u0022 is a huge volume of empty space with only slightly more rocks in it than any other volume of empty space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-10T00:11:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00226svafk.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022112.00\u0022 height=\u0022560\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/6svafk.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-10T01:31:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173320\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662766581\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022asteroid belt\u0022 is a huge volume of empty space with only slightly more rocks in it than any other volume of empty space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSlightly more in the absolute scale.\u00A0 Hugely more on the relative scale.\u00A0 Which strongly implies that all spacecraft/satellite/whatever damage comes from man-made items whizzing around space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-10T03:27:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662753782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022farmerben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, farmerben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any way to paint the outer hull with polymers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe outer holl is covered with insulation, either as panels, or as blanket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RuBisCO","CreatedById":59540,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T00:37:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadiators? How would holes in radiators in space be plugged?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T02:25:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662856672\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259540\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RuBisCO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RuBisCO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadiators? How would holes in radiators in space be plugged?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlways worked for me...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227931195_1631186815211_0.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.overeview.io/7931195_1631186815211_0.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mileage may vary....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-09-11T02:25:51Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2022 02:25  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T04:57:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662856672\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259540\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RuBisCO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, RuBisCO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadiators? How would holes in radiators in space be plugged?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022top-view-of-milk-chocolate-bars-in-foil-\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022110.66\u0022 height=\u0022436\u0022 width=\u0022394\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.istockphoto.com/photos/top-view-of-milk-chocolate-bars-in-foil-isolated-on-white-background-picture-id1054049626?k=20\u0026amp;m=1054049626\u0026amp;s=170667a\u0026amp;w=0\u0026amp;h=hV7FyXXnGa1hWwwjcfQ9y3iwofdircuHt2auCJYZGFk=\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002261-ZbvbygwL.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u00221200\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61-ZbvbygwL.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RuBisCO","CreatedById":59540,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T13:16:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do like the idea, my dudes, of putting something in the coolant (ammonia?) that will clog and seal small holes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T13:51:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmmonia is just a heat capacitor, it doesn\u0027t cool itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T14:09:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173734\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662863125\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlways worked for me...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://cdn.overeview.io/7931195_1631186815211_0.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00227931195_1631186815211_0.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.overeview.io/7931195_1631186815211_0.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mileage may vary....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does that work? I have used it but wonder on how it works its wonders. It can not be air it react to as its air in the top of the radiator.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn space the hole will be out into vacuum who might make it easier to find.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-11T15:28:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224173884\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221662905361\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does that work? I have used it but wonder on how it works its wonders. It can not be air it react to as its air in the top of the radiator.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn space the hole will be out into vacuum who might make it easier to find.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe that the particles in the hot coolant get sucked toward the hole and gum it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}